      },
      "id": 100,
      "options": {
        "content": "Business counters and Observation API timers scraped from `/actuator/prometheus` on each service. Stat totals use `round(sum(increase(...[$__range])))` because plain `increase()` extrapolates between scrapes and often returns fractional counts. Timeseries rows show rates (/s) and mean latency.\n\n**Saga semantics:** inventory reservation runs before payment. **Reserved** can exceed **Confirmed** when payment declines \u2014 stock is not automatically restored in this demo. **Reserved** counts distinct `order.created` successes (after idempotent processing), not \u201cunits on hand\u201d; with SKU qty 10 and qty 1 per order you should see at most 10 reservations before out-of-stock failures (unless you reset Prometheus while DB retained history).\n\n**Order detail cache (Redis):** Application counters **`commerce_order_service_order_detail_cache_total`** (`result=hit|miss`). Use the **Stat** tiles for **total hit/miss counts in the dashboard time range**; the **time series** below is **rate (/s)** (good for spotting bursts), not cumulative totals. Legacy Redis **`cache_gets_total`** may still appear. Detail lookups require **GET `/orders/{id}`** traffic.\n\n**Order lookups:** Counters **`commerce_order_service_order_lookup_total`** (`result=found|not_found`) from **`GET /orders/{id}`** (cache/repository hit vs miss).",
        "mode": "markdown"
      },
      "title": "",
      "type": "text"
    },
